17	//      the model, which structurally cannot see a cookie jar, never gets to "insufficient" it away.
18	//   3. ABSTAIN BY DEFAULT (Rule 6 + Rule 12 gate 4). A text-derived candidate becomes a `violation`
19	//      ONLY on an explicit, well-formed `breach` verdict for its exact id. LLM absent, timed out,
20	//      errored, silent on this id, or ambiguous -> needs_review. Never violation, never pass by default.
21	//      This is STRICTER than the port (which left non-high-risk unadjudicated findings as-is); the new
22	//      constitution forbids any text claim shipping as a violation without an adjudicated breach.
23	//   4. THE LLM CALLER IS INJECTED. This module never touches a network. `llmCall` (the real one is
