334	/**
335	 * adjudicate(verifiedCandidates, bundle, { llmCall, deadlineMs, log }) -> { findings, report }
336	 *
337	 * findings  a NEW array, ONE finding per input candidate (never mutates the input), each stamped with
338	 *           the three-state `state` (violation|needs_review|pass) and the adjudication fields
339	 *           { adjudicated, adjudication, adjudication_reason, adjudication_disproof? }. |findings| always
340	 *           equals |verifiedCandidates|: the adjudicator is filter-only and cannot invent a finding.
341	 * report    observability + stage-manifest input: counts per bucket/state, per-batch outcomes, whether
342	 *           the LLM was available and whether the deadline was hit.
