10	//   an ABSENCE claim ("we did not find X") is the class that hallucinated a 16-breach GDPR cascade; if
11	//   it MASQUERADES as an observation it would bypass the model entirely and ship as a hard violation
12	//   with nothing but a regex behind it.
13	//
14	// THE RULE THIS ENFORCES:
15	//   Evidence kind is DECLARED by the artifact, not asserted by a label. The deterministic artifact
16	//   (Constitution Rule 3) is the ground truth:
17	//     - observation  a directly-OBSERVED fact: a captured network event, a cookie-jar entry, a failing
18	//                     DOM node, a link-health probe. BYPASSES LLM adjudication (it is a fact, not a
19	//                     reading of a page). Ships as an adjudicated violation carrying its artifact.
20	//     - register     a public-REGISTER row (Companies House / ICO / SRA / ...). BYPASSES adjudication.
21	//     - absence      the TEXT-DERIVED class (a required disclosure claimed missing, OR a verbatim quote
22	//                     matched on the page and claimed to breach). This is the fabrication-prone class and
23	//                     ALWAYS requires LLM adjudication. It never bypasses.
24	//
25	//   A candidate may NEVER masquerade its kind. If a candidate DECLARES a kind (`evidence_kind`) that
26	//   disagrees with the kind its artifact actually establishes, it is REJECTED (valid:false): the
27	//   adjudicator quarantines it to needs-review rather than trust the label. A candidate with no
28	//   recognised artifact at all is rejected too (no artifact, no breach - Rule 3).
29	//
30	// This module is PURE: a function of one candidate object, no I/O, no network, no module-scope mutation.
31	
32	const { ARTIFACT_TYPES } = require('../artifact-types.js');
33	
34	// ── artifact.type families (the ground truth). A candidate BYPASSES only on a genuine observed/register
35	//    artifact type; everything text-shaped is the adjudicated `absence` class. Each set maps FROM the
36	//    canonical breach/artifact-types.js enum (the one door the proposer/verifier flow emits) and keeps
37	//    the old-estate literals as PORT ALIASES so a ported candidate or a legacy calibration fixture still
38	//    classifies correctly (ledger decision 1: "replace/alias its corpus_quote/network_request/
39	//    cookie_jar_entry literals"). Before this, the sets held ONLY the port literals, so a real proposer's
40	//    `network_event`/`coverage_proof`/`register_absence` candidate matched none of them and was silently
41	//    quarantined - the C-084 disease resurrected through a type-name mismatch. ──────────────────────────
42	//
43	// register_absence is deliberately in the TEXT (adjudicated) family, NOT the bypassing register family:
44	// a register no-match is WEAK (a slightly different registered name can miss the match), so it must be
45	// quarantined, never bypassed to a hard violation (Rule 6). Only a PRESENT register_row bypasses.
46	const OBSERVED_ARTIFACT_TYPES = new Set([
47	  ARTIFACT_TYPES.NETWORK_EVENT,
48	  'network_request', 'cookie_jar_entry', 'dom_node', 'failing_dom_node', 'link_health', // port aliases
49	]);
50	const REGISTER_ARTIFACT_TYPES = new Set([
51	  ARTIFACT_TYPES.REGISTER_ROW,
52	  'register_hit', 'register_check', // port aliases
53	]);
54	const TEXT_ARTIFACT_TYPES = new Set([
55	  ARTIFACT_TYPES.QUOTE, ARTIFACT_TYPES.COVERAGE_PROOF, ARTIFACT_TYPES.REGISTER_ABSENCE,
56	  'corpus_quote', 'verbatim_quote', 'presence', 'absence', 'absence_claim', // port aliases
57	]);
